---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Product",
  "name": "Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Biotech Centrifuge",
  "description": "Alfa Laval BTPX-205 self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge for biotech cell harvesting, pharmaceutical separation, and chemical processing. 5 GPM, 12,800 Gs.",
  "brand": { "@type": "Brand", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge" },
  "manufacturer": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge", "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com" },
  "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Biotech Centrifuge"
  description="Alfa Laval BTPX-205 self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge for biotech cell harvesting, pharmaceutical separation, and chemical processing. 5 GPM, 12,800 Gs."
  canonicalUrl="https://dolphincentrifuge.com/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/"
  breadcrumbs={[{label: 'Products', href: '/disc-stack-centrifuge/'}, {label: 'BTPX 205'}]}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy text-white">
    <div class="container-dolphin py-12 md:py-16">
      <span class="text-gold text-xs font-bold tracking-wider uppercase">Products</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold font-heading mt-2 mb-4">Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Biotech Centrifuge</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg max-w-2xl mb-6">Dolphin Centrifuge provides expert service, genuine parts, and fully reconditioned units for this model. A self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge purpose-built for biotechnology cell harvesting, pharmaceutical recovery, and fine chemical separation. The BTPX-205 delivers 12,800 Gs of centrifugal force for sub-micron particle removal at up to 5 GPM.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gold hover:bg-gold-light text-navy font-bold text-sm px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">Request a Quote</a>
        <a href="tel:2485222573" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 border border-white/30 hover:border-gold text-white font-semibold text-sm px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">(248) 522-2573</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Specs & Content -->
  <section class="bg-warm-white">
    <div class="container-dolphin py-12 md:py-16 max-w-4xl">

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The Alfa Laval BTPX-205 is a self-cleaning centrifuge of the disc stack type, engineered for the continuous separation of solids from liquids in demanding biotech and pharmaceutical environments. The machine can be configured as a purifier (liquid-liquid-solid separation) or as a clarifier (liquid-solid separation), giving operators flexibility across a wide range of process requirements.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        A key feature of the BTPX-205 is its partial solids ejection capability. Unlike full-discharge centrifuges that expel both solids and a significant volume of process fluid during each cycle, the BTPX-205 purges only the accumulated solids. This partial discharge dramatically reduces fluid losses, which is critical in pharmaceutical and biotech applications where the process fluid itself is the valuable product.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-8">
        The sludge ejection cycle can be triggered by a timer or based on the volume of fluid processed, allowing precise control over the discharge frequency. The centrifuge handles solids content up to 10% by volume in the feed stream.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Technical Specifications</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Model Type</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">Alfa Laval BTPX-205-SGD34-CDP</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Rated Capacity</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">5 GPM on Pharma Cell Broth</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Sludge Space</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">0.25 Gallons</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Bowl RPM</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">9,650</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">G-Force</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">12,800 Gs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Motor HP</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">7.5 HP</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Voltages</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">230 / 460 V</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Applications</h2>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The BTPX-205 is designed for removing suspended solids with particle sizes ranging from 0.5 to 500 &micro;m. The liquid centrate has a lower density than the separated solids, and total solids content can range from 0.1% to 10% by volume.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-3">Biotechnology</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-text-light space-y-2">
            <li>&#8226; Organic cell harvesting</li>
            <li>&#8226; Cell growth media clarification</li>
            <li>&#8226; Fermentation broth clarification</li>
            <li>&#8226; Cell debris removal</li>
            <li>&#8226; Inclusion body recovery</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-3">Pharmaceutical</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-text-light space-y-2">
            <li>&#8226; Plasma fraction recovery</li>
            <li>&#8226; Precipitate recovery</li>
            <li>&#8226; Vaccines and serums production</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-3">Chemical</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-text-light space-y-2">
            <li>&#8226; Catalyst separation</li>
            <li>&#8226; Sub-micron particle separation</li>
            <li>&#8226; Pigments, dyes, and toners</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">How It Works</h2>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The bio-culture fluid enters the rotating bowl of the BTPX-205 centrifuge. The bowl generates an extreme centrifugal force of 12,800 Gs, causing rapid sedimentation of suspended cells and particles.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The process fluid enters through a stationary inlet pipe and is accelerated by a distributor before entering the disc stack. Separation occurs in the inter-disc spaces where solids migrate outward toward the bowl periphery while the clarified liquid moves toward the center. A paring disc pumps the clear centrate out of the bowl under pressure.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The accumulated solids are ejected through ports at the bowl periphery via a hydraulic mechanism that forces a sliding piston downward. A cyclone at the discharge reduces the high ejection velocity of the solids, preserving the integrity of sensitive biological materials.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-light mb-8">
        The separated cells and solids are auto-ejected while the liquid phase (broth) exits through a separate outlet, enabling continuous, unattended operation.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Why Choose the BTPX-205?</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-2">Minimal Product Loss</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-light">Partial discharge technology ejects only solids, dramatically reducing the loss of valuable process fluid compared to full-discharge centrifuges.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-2">Extreme G-Force</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-light">At 12,800 Gs, the BTPX-205 separates particles as small as 0.5 microns, making it ideal for cell harvesting and fine precipitate recovery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-2">Continuous Operation</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-light">Self-cleaning design with programmable discharge intervals allows uninterrupted processing without manual intervention.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy mb-2">Versatile Configuration</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-light">Can be set up as a clarifier or purifier to match specific process requirements in biotech, pharma, and chemical applications.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Related Resources</h2>
      <ul class="text-text-light space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>&#8226; <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">Disc Stack Centrifuge Overview</a></li>
        <li>&#8226; <a href="/food-grade-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">Food Grade Centrifuge Systems</a></li>
        <li>&#8226; <a href="/alfa-laval-stainless-steel-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">Stainless Steel Centrifuges</a></li>
        <li>&#8226; <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-applications/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">All Centrifuge Applications</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-text-light mb-8">
        <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">Looking for a complete turnkey system? See our disc stack centrifuge systems &rarr;</a>
      </p>

      <!-- Bottom CTA -->
      <div class="bg-navy rounded-xl p-8 text-center mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Interested in This Centrifuge?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 max-w-lg mx-auto">Contact our team for pricing, availability, and system configuration options for the Alfa Laval BTPX-205.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="bg-gold hover:bg-gold-light text-navy font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">Get a Quote</a>
          <a href="tel:2485222573" class="border border-white/30 hover:border-gold text-white font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">(248) 522-2573</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
